SevaConnect – AI-Powered Healthcare Scheme Assistant
🧩 Problem :
Accessing government healthcare schemes like PMJAY is difficult for many users due to:
Low awareness of eligibility criteria
Complex documentation requirements
Language and literacy barriers
Difficulty finding nearby empanelled hospitals
This leads to low adoption of available benefits, especially in underserved communities.
💡 Solution :
Designed an AI-powered assistant that helps users:
Check eligibility
Understand required documents
Discover nearby hospitals
Interact in multiple languages (voice + text)
🎯 My Role :.
Defined product vision and user problem
Designed end-to-end user journey
Built conversational flow logic
Focused on accessibility and usability
⚙️ Key Features :
Multilingual conversational interface (voice + text)
Guided eligibility checker
Document requirement assistant
Location-based hospital discovery
🧪 Product Thinking :
User Persona
Low-income individuals
Limited digital literacy
Prefer regional languages
Key Insight
“Users don’t fail to access schemes because they don’t qualify—they fail because the process is too complex.”
📈 Impact :
Simplified a multi-step government process into a guided flow
Reduced user effort in discovering and applying for schemes
Improved accessibility through multilingual and voice support
🚀 Future Improvements :
Integration with government databases
Real-time application tracking
WhatsApp-based interface for wider reach
